-- Colombian Stocks: Canacol, Ecopetrol, ISA, Pacific Rubiales
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-06-12T20:49:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-12/colombian-stocks-canacol-ecopetrol-isa-pacific-rubiales.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  fell 1 percent to 13,901.89, while the
Colcap Index dropped 1 percent to 1,656.57. Colombian markets
were closed yesterday for a holiday.  Interconexion Electrica SA (ISA)   dropped 2.6 percent to
10,620 pesos. The Prosperity Highway project will be assigned
through a public auction after ISA didn’t meet the necessary
legal requirements, Colombian President  Juan Manuel Santos  said,
according to an e-mailed statement. The Colombian energy and
highway company can take part in the public auction to build the
project, Caracol Radio said today, citing an interview with
Mines and Energy Minister  Mauricio Cardenas .  Colombia’s oil output dropped to 936,052 barrels a day in
May from 955,000 barrels in April, Cardenas told reporters in
Cartagena on June 8. May output was hampered by infrastructure
and transport difficulties, according to an e-mailed statement.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest  oil company ,
fell 1.5 percent to 5,150 pesos.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE) 
, which operates the country’s largest oil field,
dropped 1.8 percent to 43,420 pesos.  Petrominerales Ltd. (PMG)  , a Calgary-based oil company that operates in the Andean
region, decreased 5.5 percent to 21,560 pesos.  Canacol Energy
Ltd. (CNEC)  , the Calgary-based oil company that operates
fields in Colombia, slumped 7.8 percent to 1,000 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christine Jenkins in Bogota at 
 cjenkins28@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
